{ "id": 1540236, "name": "Computer Literacy (PC)", "summary": "The Computer literacy test is meant to evaluate basic knowledge and ability to use computers and related technology in a workplace environment. This test helps you identify candidates who are ready to perform basic work functions on a computer.", "duration": 540.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Computer literacy, including the ability to use computers and maintain a basic understanding of how they operate, is an important ability in the modern workplace environment. Employees who have computer literacy have the ability to use computers and related technology efficiently, and are comfortable using computers and applications to perform workplace functions. \n\nThis Computer literacy (PC) test allows you to identify candidates who possess a basic ability to use computers for a variety of workplace tasks, and to use them safely and efficiently in real-life, workplace contexts. To answer the questions in the test successfully, candidates must understand the basics of computer operations, Internet navigation, e-mail, and file & folder handling using a Windows (PC) operating system.\n\nThe test requires candidates to identify the right answers to the questions in a limited amount of time. Successful candidates can understand and interpret basic computer menus and settings options quickly and accurately, access and navigate the Internet safely and efficiently, use email effectively, manage their disk space, and select the appropriate applications to use for a variety of basic workplace tasks. Candidates are not only evaluated on fundamental concepts, but are also tested on common features and safe usage practices. This is a great test to include in evaluating candidates' basic technical skills and computer use.", "relevant": "Any role that involves basic computer use, including entry- to mid-level workers in a variety of roles from customer service representatives to administrative assistants, receptionists, and health information technicians.", "job_roles": [ 1889, 1970, 1511, 2051, 2069, 2153, 1559, 2219, 2402, 1634, 2462, 2633, 1724, 2771, 2846, 1757, 2972, 1778, 3190 ], "owner": { "id": 257211, "biography": "The global IT industry has benefited from Anirban’s talents for over two decades. { "id": 389, "name": "Microsoft Windows", "summary": "This Microsoft Windows test evaluates candidates' understanding and application of basic concepts in Windows. It helps you hire candidates who are comfortable working in Windows as the framework for the Microsoft Office suite of software.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Microsoft Windows is one of the world’s most popular operating systems and has long been the standard operating system used in the business world. With most office jobs currently requiring the use of computers, Microsoft Windows has become even more important for managing business operations, ensuring a good workflow, and achieving efficiency and productivity. This test is especially pertinent to roles that use the Microsoft Office suite at the core of their business operations. \n\nThe Microsoft Windows test assesses candidates’ abilities to handle files in Windows File Explorer, to apply basic functions of Windows in various situations, and to understand the basic terminology of the Windows operating system. The test uses scenarios often encountered in a business setting to evaluate candidates’ skills in using the most commonly used features of Microsoft Windows. \n\nCandidates who perform well on this test possess a good understanding of the Microsoft Windows operating system and are comfortable using it daily in their work. These candidates can operate the system with ease and accuracy and build productive workflows for themselves. They can easily create, locate, and manipulate files and programs to achieve results.", "relevant": "Administrative assistants, executive assistants, and any job roles that require a good command of the Windows operating system.", "job_roles": [ 1463, 1889, 1562, 2402, 1610, 2720, 1724, 2795, 2849, 1757, 2909, 2912 ], "owner": { "id": 733, "biography": "IT support manager Miranda possesses a demonstrated history of supporting cutting-edge software in high-growth, fast-paced environments. { "id": 691565, "name": "Google Slides", "summary": "This Google Slides test evaluates candidates’ technical knowledge of the tool and their ability to design and build appealing slide decks, all while taking smart and efficient approaches to doing so.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "A well-defined project roadmap plan, a creative pitch for a new product, and a clear, well-structured infographic presenting interesting data and findings are all artifacts that are commonly created with Google Slides. A strong level of understanding of Google Slides’ functionalities and the ability to design a cohesive slide deck are essential for crafting a powerful presentation.\n \nThe Google Slides test for professionals assesses candidates’ knowledge of the various features Google Slides has to offer. Through questions that focus and expand on the different core functions of the tool, this test evaluates candidates’ ability to create and display objects and visual assets, their skills in structuring and arranging the latter within slides, and their knowledge of productivity and collaboration features within Google Slides.\n \nCandidates who perform well on this test know how to use Google Slides proficiently, utilizing core layout and design functions. They know how to order slides and distribute components within them in favor of more harmonious presentations. The test ensures that these candidates can also create slide decks that clearly and logically communicate business goals, objectives, initiatives, and results within your company in a clear and efficient manner, boosting productivity and increasing alignment within your teams.", "relevant": "Analysts, management consultants, marketing representatives, product managers, project managers, sales representatives, business development representatives", "job_roles": [ 1994, 1598, 2675, 5944, 2825, 2843, 2951, 5159 ], "owner": { "id": 353470, "biography": "Michel has navigated various industries, from SaaS to Enterprise Technology, and has been part of the founding team for multiple organizations. Primarily working in Product Management and being involved in the Startup space, he has learnt a great deal on how to shape and present new initiatives. Be it for a new product or initiative, Michel enjoys channeling his creativity and experience into communicating ideas impactfully, setting them up for success.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/d7818c50-4f0e-4abc-ac2b-441744df9d20-aca392ef-58d0-42f4-9889-3c31e5bcd004.png", "full_name": "Michel N.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 717198, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 717194, "description": "Creating a cohesive deck", "preview": false }, { "id": 717195, "description": "Utilizing visual and layout features", "preview": false }, { "id": 717196, "description": "Creating and manipulating objects", "preview": false }, { "id": 717197, "description": "Leveraging productivity and collaboration features", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 431881, "text": "

You are a technology product owner at your company. Senior management has invited all of the company’s product owners to present their annual results and plans for the upcoming year at tomorrow’s meeting. You are outlining your presentation and want to limit the presentation to four key slides.

 

Which of the following outlines will be the most effective for your presentation?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 5802925, "text": "

Last year’s roadmap > This year’s product roadmap > Evolution of user metrics > Evolution of product metrics

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 5802926, "text": "

Product intro > Motivation behind product > Evolution of product metrics > This year’s product roadmap

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 5802927, "text": "

Evolution of user metrics > Evolution of product metrics > Last year’s product roadmap > This year’s product roadmap

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 5802928, "text": "

Motivation behind product > Last year’s product roadmap > This year’s product roadmap > Evolution of product metrics

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 717198, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 431881, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 431882, "text": "

Tomorrow, you are leading a presentation that includes three guest speakers. Each speaker has sent you an avatar to use as a headshot. You have added them to your slide below, but you want to spread out the images across the length of the slide.

 

Which steps should you take?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 5802929, "text": "

Select all the images, then right-click. From the menu that appears, click Distribute > Horizontally.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 5802930, "text": "

Select all the images, then right-click. From the menu that appears, click Align > Center.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 5802931, "text": "

Move the rightmost picture to the far right of the slide, then Select all and use the Distribute function.

{ "id": 830762, "name": "Merchandise Planner", "summary": "This Merchandise Planner test evaluates candidates’ quantitative skills and their ability to support the sales and margin goals of the business. This screening test will help you hire merchandise planners capable of developing effective merchandise plans.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today’s highly competitive retail environment, it is paramount that businesses be able to optimally select, manage, display, and price products. A retailer’s goal should be to maximize returns on investment, add value to the brand name and satisfy customer needs – all while avoiding the creation of excess inventory. Hiring a highly qualified merchandise planner can help your retail business achieve these goals. Candidates with merchandise planner skills can serve as business managers for specific product categories and provide decision-making support for their buying partners in your business. By building sound, well-thought-out seasonal plans, merchandise planners create a framework within which the buyer is able to focus on curating an optimal assortment for the customer. \n\nRetail is a fast-paced and fluid business and requires the ability to constantly evaluate and adjust, based on results. { "id": 929611, "name": "Business Operations Management", "summary": "This Business Operations Management test evaluates candidates’ ability to plan, organize, and control operations. This screening test will help you hire business operations managers who can manage productivity, inventory, and the supply chain.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Every organization needs a person responsible for the smooth running of its business operations and the effective use of resources. Candidates who perform well on this test are likely to possess a strong knowledge of the skills required to organize, plan, and control business operations, and manage productivity, inventory, and the supply chain. Successful candidates will be able to help your organization by assessing and improving existing processes, resources, and capacities. They will also possess the ability to design, evaluate, and update controls, and will be able to help organizations detect and prevent errors.\n\nThis test includes evaluation of candidates’ ability to design approaches to work and design measurement of work. It looks at scheduling and quality management, as well as purchasing processes and stock management.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify business operations managers who will be responsible for planning and controlling inventory, the supply chain, and production. They will also be able to provide detailed production and procurement plans and enhance productivity by proactively addressing all key business operations issues.", "relevant": "This test will be relevant for operations managers, production managers, project managers, supply chain managers, and sole proprietors and entrepreneurs taking care of their business operations.", "job_roles": [ 4304, 2480, 2507, 6308 ], "owner": { "id": 481251, "biography": "Abdul is a chartered accountant with over 15 years' experience in accounting, finance, auditing and risk management with global companies such as Ernst & Young. Abdul has significant consulting experience, having worked in the oil and gas, pharmaceuticals, food, and education sectors. He has also worked as a university lecturer in accounting, finance, and tax-related subjects, and currently works on complex risk management policies as a senior risk management officer.", "country": 87, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/2a4a3926-09e1-4526-bc99-87baf6cbb881-bed8e85a-fa4d-43ab-9261-aad30e70bfa7.png", "full_name": "Abdul G.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 963015, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 963011, "description": "Operations design and organization", "preview": false }, { "id": 963012, "description": "Planning and control", "preview": false }, { "id": 963013, "description": "Inventory and supply chain management", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 652415, "text": "

Jamie is working as a storekeeper at your company on a monthly salary of $2,000. Along with recording movement of inventory, he is also responsible for conducting physical inventory counts at the end of each month and updating the records accordingly. At year-end, external auditors identified that the inventory in store was lower than the inventory shown in the accounts.


Which of the following actions should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6890877, "text": "

Assign the monthly inventory count to Jamie’s co-worker.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890878, "text": "

Arrange for the monthly inventory count to be carried out by the external auditors and Jamie at the same time.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890879, "text": "

Arrange a training session for the auditors to enhance their understanding of your company’s business.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890880, "text": "

Increase Jamie's salary by 25%.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 963015, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 652415, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 652416, "text": "

You are working as an operations manager at a zoo. Entry to the zoo is gained via two entrances, each with their own queue. However, due to a seasonal shortage of ticketing staff, visitors in both queues have to wait for up to 15 minutes before entering. As a result, many visitors are getting frustrated and you have received many complaints. 


Which of the following measures should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6890881, "text": "

Add 'estimated queue time from this point' signs to the queuing area.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890882, "text": "

Allow visitors to switch between queues.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890883, "text": "

Allow visitors who threaten to register formal complaints to enter first.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890884, "text": "

Install video screens showing videos of different animals in the zoo.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6890885, "text": "

Allow visitors to enter without security checks.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 963015, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 652416, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 652417, "text": "

Which other option should you suggest?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6890886, "text": "

“Let's ensure we are fully compliant in terms of corporate governance.”

{ "id": 948756, "name": "Administrative Assistant", "summary": "This Administrative Assistant test evaluates a candidate’s ability to support your business. This screening test will help you hire an administrative assistant who can increase the day-to-day efficiency and organization of your team’s work.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "From making sure your teams work effectively together to maintaining strong and consistent communication channels and making sure internal business processes and practices are adhered to, an administrative assistant isn’t just necessary for your organization to run smoothly; they can help transform how it runs. \n\nThis test evaluates candidates’ abilities to communicate effectively and efficiently with both internal and external stakeholders. It also assesses if the candidates have the requisite knowledge to effectively organize and manage their time. Additionally, the test will appraise their attention to detail, as well as their ability to solve problems through their critical and independent thinking skills. \n\nThis screening test will help you identify proven and experienced administrative assistants who can not only provide direct support to your organization, but who can also help improve your everyday processes to boost the way you do business.", "relevant": "Administrative assistants, executive administrative assistants, project assistants, project coordinators, team support.", "job_roles": [ 1889, 2069, 4337, 5922, 2402, 1649, 4639, 4688, 2633, 4733, 4758, 3655, 4832, 5143, 3167 ], "owner": { "id": 487146, "biography": "Research Director and Program Evaluator Liam has spent 15 years in leading administrative roles, working for 13 companies across 12 sectors including fundraising and development, fintech, recruitment, not-for-profit organizations, research, higher education, and museums and heritage.\n\nLiam has been described as a Swiss army knife of skills and experiences, bringing the analytical skills developed during his PhD to help companies find that extra organizational edge.", "country": 32, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/429e2f73-b3e3-4038-99ee-e24a5f3f8ca6-8de92392-705c-4997-bcb8-1d2a6149c9ed.png", "full_name": "Liam K.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 983961, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 983962, "description": "Verbal and Written Communication", "preview": false }, { "id": 983963, "description": "Organization and Time Management", "preview": false }, { "id": 983964, "description": "Attention to Detail", "preview": false }, { "id": 983965, "description": "Problem Solving", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 705258, "text": "

They have asked you to turn it into an email that will be sent out to all employees, including those who weren’t in attendance.

 

What are the most appropriate actions you should take before sending out the email?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7083526, "text": "

Type up the notes, reformat into long-form, copyedit, send out the email

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083528, "text": "

Type up the short-form notes word for word, send out the email

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083529, "text": "

Type up the notes, reformat into long-form, copyedit, send to the CEO for review, send out the email

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 983961, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2044593, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 658687, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 2 }, { "id": 705259, "text": "

What is the most appropriate action for you to take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7083530, "text": "

Check that calendars are up-to-date, and that all are able to make the meetings.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083532, "text": "

Ask the client if a later presentation date is possible.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083533, "text": "

Check team members’ calendars to see if they are available for the presentation.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 983961, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2044594, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 658688, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 2 }, { "id": 705260, "text": "

 You are supporting a growth manager. It is late on a Friday, and she has asked you to email three prospective clients to set up meetings for early next week. She forwarded you the email template, but is now unreachable and will be for the next few hours. You have reviewed the email template and realize that it may contain factual errors, although you need to confirm.


What action should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7083536, "text": "

Send the emails as is.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083537, "text": "

Message the unreachable growth manager and wait for her response before sending the emails.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7083538, "text": "

Reach out to one of the growth department’s administrative assistants to confirm before sending the emails.

You’ve been invited to give a presentation at a professional conference. The audience consists of individuals from diverse backgrounds, including different industries and professional levels.


Which of the following approaches would be most effective in communicating with this audience?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8937423, "text": "

Present concepts to simple terms and make the presentation interactive by asking and answering questions.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937424, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937425, "text": "

Establish your expertise and relevance by referencing the latest buzzwords and trending topics in your industry

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937426, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1243484, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1047535, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1047538, "text": "

You’re a team manager, and you receive an email from one of your team members requesting immediate time off for personal reasons. The email is brief and urgent, but lacks specific details about the dates or the reason for the time off. This team member is typically reliable and has never sent an email like this before.


How should you respond to the email?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8937427, "text": "

Request more specific information, such as the dates and why they need the time off, before you approve the request.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937428, "text": "

Approve the time off immediately to accommodate the urgency without seeking further details.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937429, "text": "

Forward the email to the HR department and ask them to handle the request.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937430, "text": "

Acknowledge the request and ask them to provide more information at their earliest convenience.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1243484, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1047538, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1047539, "text": "

“Your work is fantastic overall, but you really need to focus on your writing. Every document you’ve submitted is incredibly unprofessional.”


Which of the following options shows how they should revise this feedback?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8937431, "text": "

“Your work is fantastic overall. You don't know how to write professionally, though. Here are examples of where you could have done better.”

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937432, "text": "

“Your work is fantastic overall. I wish you would write professionally, though. Your documents aren't of the quality we expect from someone with your potential.”

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937433, "text": "

“Your work is fantastic overall. You need to learn how to write professionally, though. Please review your documents for improvements.”

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937434, "text": "

“Your work is fantastic overall. Writing professionally, though, is an area you can improve on. Here are examples of where you could have done better.”

You’re meeting with a colleague who starts complaining about recent policy changes at the company you both work for. You agree with most of what they’re saying, and you know that the changes have made their job more difficult. You also know that some of the policy changes have solved problems both you and your colleague have often faced.


What is the best way to demonstrate empathy for your colleague?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8937435, "text": "

Remind them of the positive aspects of the policy changes and suggest ways to adapt to the new circumstances.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937436, "text": "

Suggest that the policy changes are beneficial overall and change the subject to a more positive topic.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937437, "text": "

Paraphrase what they have said and discuss how policy changes have both benefited and made things difficult for you.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937438, "text": "

Downplay their concerns and emphasize the benefits of the policy changes for the company.

{ "id": 603719, "name": "SketchUp Pro", "summary": "This SketchUp Pro test evaluates candidates’ abilities with the software and their ability to create detailed and organized 3D models for presentations and photorealistic renderings. This hiring test identifies skilled, intermediate SketchUp Pro users.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Whether used for the architectural industry or product manufacturers, companies want to visually see their product before it’s built, and 3D visualization provides this solution. 3D models in SketchUp Pro allow potential buyers or manufacturers to see, adjust, and change what their product will look like. With the advent of 3D printing, 3D modeling has become even more relevant as it can provide quick study models and photorealistic renders to present to a potential client. One of the most important pieces of software for 3D modeling is SketchUp Pro by Trimble.\n\nThis SketchUp Pro screening test assesses candidates’ knowledge of the software’s key functionalities. This hiring test uses questions that focus on a user’s ability to model geometry, make changes efficiently and effectively, and listen and respond to customers’ needs. Through SketchUp Pro basics, solid geometry modeling, creating and handling complex geometry, and pro tools and modeling tricks, this hiring test will help you identify SketchUp Pro practitioners who are skilled and fast at this important work.\n\nCandidates who perform well on this hiring test have skills and experience using SketchUp Pro and can successfully complete and manipulate complex 3D models. This hiring test ensures you will hire candidates with all the necessary technical and working SketchUp skills, leading to the production of accurate and renderable 3D assets with speed and precision. \n\nSketchUp Pro was known for many years as Google SketchUp or Google SketchUp Pro, until the software was purchased by Trimble in 2012. Even today, many professionals still collequentialy refer to the software as Google SketchUp Pro, even though Trimble Inc. owns and manages the software. No matter the terminology, this hiring test will allow you to find the SketchUp expert to help your business.", "relevant": "Architects, 3D visualizers, Interior designers, Fitout designers, Furniture modelers, and others use who SketchUp Pro.", "job_roles": [ 5305, 5306, 5734, 1871, 5737, 1481, 1928, 4112, 4113, 4119, 3239, 4131, 1988, 5360, 5366, 3323, 5368, 5369, 5370, 3325, 5372, 3326, 5383, 5384, 4221, 1559, 2309, 3384, 2312, 4294, 1598, 3387, 4303, 4307, 3400, 4323, 3414, 5445, 4355, 3467, 5470, 5471, 5744, 3478, 5481, 4432, 4434, 3498, 5490, 2489, 2492, 5505, 3507, 4595, 3568, 4599, 4607, 3574, 4625, 4631, 4632, 4676, 4677, 5536, 5544, 4702, 3629, 3640, 3646, 5745, 5746, 3654, 4759, 3666, 4768, 4769, 4770, 3678, 4793, 5747, 3699, 4808, 3708, 5588, 3709, 6311, 3715, 6324, 6325, 6079, 6328, 4863, 5612, 5615, 3762, 4882, 4883, 2819, 4887, 4891, 3768, 4893, 4899, 4904, 4909, 5628, 4981, 3814, 4997, 3816, 5001, 5002, 5003, 3818, 3819, 5650, 3829, 5039, 3836, 5044, 5666, 5077, 5093, 5112, 5118, 5134, 5147, 5152, 5689, 3907, 5178, 5179, 5195, 5207, 3937, 3941, 5728, 3942, 5730, 5229, 3170, 3945, 5257 ], "owner": { "id": 302162, "biography": "Hamza has a decade of experience working as an architect in various design firms, and he relishes being involved in every architectural stage, from developing a concept to actual execution. Which of the following is the most likely reason your efforts to create a solid group failed?

Statistics and probability are at the core of data analysis, driving discoveries in science and helping businesses to make data-driven decisions. Regardless of your field or industry, hiring an expert with knowledge of statistics and probability will allow you to understand your subject more deeply and make predictions about the world. \n\nThis Fundamentals of Statistics and Probability test uses applied examples to test candidates’ knowledge in core areas of statistics such as descriptive statistics, random variables, sampling techniques, estimation methods, and inferential statistics. \n\nCandidates who perform well on this Fundamentals of Statistics and Probability test have a strong grasp of statistical and probabilistic concepts, and they know how to apply these concepts to solve real-world problems in a variety of fields. { "id": 1950152, "name": "Clean Code", "summary": "Clean code is the hallmark of a quality software engineer. It can be the difference between wasting thousands on a project versus doing it right the first time. This screening test validates an engineer’s ability to write easy to maintain code.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 7, "name": "Programming skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "As an engineer, the last thing you want to refactor is spaghetti code. It is time-consuming, wastes client funds, and is often one of the worst parts of writing code. Clean code, which is all about being clear, simple, and efficient, doesn't just make a software product work better - it also speeds up the whole development process. When engineers focus on clean code, they make software that's easier to update and maintain. This saves time and resources down the line, letting businesses respond faster to what customers want, keeping them ahead of the game. Plus, clean code means fewer bugs and errors, so products are more reliable, building trust with customers. Ultimately, clean code means lower development costs, higher productivity, happier customers, and a better edge in the market. So, engineers who care about clean code aren't just tech whizzes - they're key players driving a business's success and growth.\n\nThis Clean Code hiring test evaluates the candidate’s conceptual understanding of clean code principles through real-world scenario-based, language-agnostic questions. It measures an engineer’s ability to write clean code with regards to formatting and style, control flow and logic, modularity and code organization, and software design principles.\n\nUse this test to recruit and hire developers skilled at clean code concepts. You have an application running on an EC2 instance that requires access to read/write to a DynamoDB table. 


Which of the following is a secure way for the EC2 instance to access the DynamoDB table?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 11237235, "text": "

Since the EC2 instance and the DynamoDB table are owned by the same AWS account, they can communicate with each other by default.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 11237236, "text": "

Generate API keys with access to the DynamoDB table, and use the API keys in your application.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 11237237, "text": "

Create an IAM user with the proper permissions, and associate the user with the EC2 instance.

This Visual Basic for Applications test uses real-world scenarios to gauge practical and applied VBA skills.\n\nThis VBA test focuses on core VBA skills, including using intermediate coding, applying visual UserForms, working with data from varying sources, and using VBA with Microsoft Excel, one of the most popular applications of VBA.\n\nVBA is useful for a variety of business sectors, and developing the right tools may save your company hundreds of hours, as VBA enables repetitive tasks to be replaced with scripts, forms, functions, and procedures. VBA can help you save time and money by implementing efficient coding, managing data inside Excel sheets, connecting with SQL databases, and reading HTML and visual creations. { "id": 912422, "name": "Apache Spark for Data Engineers", "summary": "This Apache Spark for Data Engineers test evaluates a candidate’s ability to use Apache Spark for large-scale data processing. This hiring test will help you hire data engineers who have practical experience using the Spark framework.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 7, "name": "Programming skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today’s era of big data, businesses need powerful tools to process and transform it, and Apache Spark is one of the most powerful tools available today for big data operations. Since its release in 2009, its use has exponentially ramped up among companies that work with some of the largest datasets. Though one of Spark’s key advantages is its ease of use, it takes an experienced data engineer to make the best use of all of its features. When you hire data engineers already well-versed in Apache Spark, your data projects will be completed more quickly, allowing your business to focus on implementing the solutions that the data implies.\n\nThis Apache Spark for Data Engineers test evaluates candidates’ abilities to apply their understanding of Apache Spark fundamentals, use Apache Spark for data transformation and processing, use Spark Core, and use Spark Streaming/Graph X. \n\nThis screening test will help you identify data engineers and other professionals who have strong experience with the Spark framework. Candidates who do well on this test will be able to efficiently problem-solve and execute on common Apache Spark scenarios they are likely to encounter on the job.", "relevant": "Data engineers", "job_roles": [ 2282, 2288 ], "owner": { "id": 472292, "biography": "A Spark data engineer with years of experience in the data field, Hamza has worked on a wide variety of machine learning, data engineering, and web scraping projects, both big and small. ", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6786121, "text": "

CNNs can read pixel by pixel for image data, while regular neural networks can’t.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6786122, "text": "

Regular neural networks are more complex to perform inferences on than CNNs.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6786123, "text": "

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6786124, "text": "

{ "id": 1354517, "name": "Data Analytics in Google Cloud Platform (GCP)", "summary": "This Data Analytics in Google Cloud Platform (GCP) test evaluates a candidate's ability to use, manage, and optimize data analysis procedures on GCP, helping hire experts who can drive data-driven decisions for your organization.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today's data-driven landscape, effectively harnessing the potential of data analytics is paramount for informed decision-making. Data analytics forms the bedrock of sound choices, and Google Cloud Platform (GCP) provides a robust framework for advanced cloud-based data analytics.\n\nThis Data Analytics in Google Cloud Platform (GCP) test rigorously evaluates candidates' abilities to design, implement, and optimize data analytics processes within the GCP ecosystem. It encompasses proficiency in four core skill areas: Data Ingestion & Storage, Data Transformation & Processing, Data Analysis & Visualization, and Performance Optimization & Cost Management.\n\nCandidates excelling in this screening test will demonstrate a profound understanding of data analytics methodologies and their adept application across diverse data sources, leveraging GCP's advanced data services. ", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9471187, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1328211, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1128843, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1128844, "text": "

You want to write a query on a large customer transactions table in Snowflake to find the five customers with the highest total transaction amounts. The transactions table consists of four columns: transaction_id (INT), customer_id (INT), transaction_amount (DECIMAL), and transaction_date (DATE).

 

How should you write a query to retrieve and present this information?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9471191, "text": "
SELECT customer_id, SUM(transaction_amount) AS total_amount\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY customer_id\nORDER BY total_amount DESC\nLIMIT 5;\n
", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9471192, "text": "
SELECT customer_id, MAX(transaction_amount) AS max_amount\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY customer_id\nORDER BY max_amount DESC\nLIMIT 5;\n
", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9471193, "text": "
SELECT customer_id, COUNT(*) AS transaction_count\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY customer_id\nORDER BY transaction_count DESC\nLIMIT 5;\n
", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9471194, "text": "
SELECT customer_id, AVG(transaction_amount) AS average_amount\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY customer_id\nORDER BY average_amount DESC\nLIMIT 5;\n
", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1328211, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1128844, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1128847, "text": "

While monitoring Snowflake performance, you noticed that a few queries – which are using a small warehouse – are taking longer than expected to execute due to high concurrency and resource contention. As a result, users are experiencing significant delays. You want to resolve this performance issue while keeping costs in mind.


What should you do first?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9471311, "text": "

Switch to a large warehouse.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9471312, "text": "

Switch to an extra-large warehouse.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9471313, "text": "

Switch to a medium warehouse.

Which of these actions should you take in response to the report? 

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6528614, "text": "

{ "id": 598357, "name": "B2C Growth Marketing (Ecommerce)", "summary": "This growth marketing test evaluates the depth and breadth of candidates’ multi-domain marketing knowledge and their ability to diagnose growth barriers, develop growth plans, and implement them for a B2C or an ecommerce business.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "If your organization is in a competitive market and is aiming for growth, creating a new revenue center, or is launching a new product, you will need help from a new breed of marketing professionals: growth marketers.\n\nGrowth marketers bring deep experience in multiple areas of marketing. They possess the power to analyze and improve your entire digital footprint, end-to-end customer journey, and shopping cart experience while pinpointing key weaknesses and optimization opportunities—large and small—to help you reach your goals.\n\nGrowth marketing is frequently a driver of digital transformation, helping you become more humble and agile as an organization, addressing strategic and tactical needs, identifying and closing weaknesses related to strategy or tactical channel implementation across primary B2C channels.\n\nCandidates who perform well on this test have the breadth and depth of knowledge across multiple marketing specialties, rounding into a comprehensive marketing generalist profile. They approach problem-solving pragmatically and possess hands-on technical skills, such as optimization, testing, and experimental design.\n\nFind out which candidate is an ultimate growth marketing machine. As a senior team member, a growth marketer brings a complete skill set across multiple marketing disciplines, can understand and analyze any part of the funnel, devise a plan to improve any metric from any channel, and help implement them using advanced skills in several specific channels.", "relevant": "Growth marketers and managers in B2C and/or eCommerce businesses, as well as anyone else who needs growth marketing skills", "job_roles": [ 1898, 6008, 2039, 2156, 2174, 1865, 2339, 6020, 6232, 6144, 2342, 2495, 2498, 2501, 2504, 2525, 2528, 2540, 2669, 2672, 2675, 1835, 4748, 2687, 5944, 2693, 4812, 2828, 2831 ], "owner": { "id": 10796, "biography": "Olena Danilchenko is a senior marketing strategist with 25+ years of international experience building and growing highly performing marketing and consulting teams in F500, innovative startups, Digital Marketing Agencies, Big 4 Consulting, and finally, her own US-based advisory practice. { "id": 380, "name": "WooCommerce", "summary": "The WooCommerce test assesses the extent to which candidates are conversant with important concepts and practices. The test assesses whether they are able to build good eCommerce solutions in WooCommerce and develop features that meet your requirements.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 7, "name": "Programming skills", "visible": true }, { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "WooCommerce has the highest market share in eCommerce, surpassing Shopify and Magento. There are over a thousand WooCommerce plugins and themes available to customize your eCommerce platform. The open-source nature and the ability to expand functionalities to enable new use cases have contributed to its popularity.\n\nMany developers have gained some experience with WooCommerce and may claim to be a pro. The low entry barriers make it relatively difficult to distinguish the skilled from the unskilled.\n\nThis test helps you to assess the WooCommerce competency of candidates, including theme development, plugin development, and eCommerce solution development. Successful candidates can help you add new features to your WooCommerce site, fix problems quickly, and find proper solutions. This test also assesses eCommerce security capabilities and SEO knowledge to help you drive sustainable growth.", "relevant": "WooCommerce developers", "job_roles": [ 2111, 3179, 3182, 3185 ], "owner": { "id": 730, "biography": "Wasim’s impressive range of e-commerce solutions demonstrates the breadth of his achievements in web development. Candidates will be evaluated on their ability to identify potential markets, engage with their community, and develop effective community plans. Additionally, candidates will be tested on their ability to communicate and moderate effectively, including managing customer feedback and conflicts. Candidates will also be evaluated on their ability to manage content, including creating, deploying, and reviewing content. Finally, candidates will be tested on their ability to analyze data and analytics, including measuring success and KPIs, and analyzing trends in the community.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify social media community management professionals who have the necessary skills and experience to excel in your organization. { "id": 540679, "name": "Content strategy", "summary": "This content strategy test evaluates a candidate’s ability to resonate with the right audience and grow qualified traffic that converts through content. { "id": 1056388, "name": "Environmental, Social, and Governance Investing", "summary": "This Environmental, Social, and Governance Investing test evaluates a candidate’s ability to make decisions in real-life scenarios relevant to environmental, social, and governance investing.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Environmental, social, and governance (ESG) investing is at the forefront of responsible business practices. Integrating ESG considerations into business decisions has become standard practice for multiple industries and companies, and the scope is expanding. Clients, regulators, and competitors are increasing pressure on investment managers to incorporate ESG principles into their strategies. \n\nThis ESG Investing test evaluates candidates’ abilities to discern and select different ESG investment approaches; choose the right ESG strategy for different asset classes; embed ESG practices across the entire investment process; and use an ESG lens to analyze and evaluate companies. \n\nCandidates who perform well on this test will be well-equipped to understand key ESG investment approaches. They can help you navigate the complexities of this new and important frontier in the practice of responsible business so that you can employ ESG strategies with confidence.", "relevant": "ESG analysts, ESG investment strategists, portfolio managers, sustainability managers, impact investment officers, and other job roles that require a strong grasp of ESG investing.", "job_roles": [ 1880, 3354, 2471, 4637, 4638, 4639, 4640, 4641, 3585, 3190 ], "owner": { "id": 558926, "biography": "Özge is a certified ESG and sustainability analyst, trained by a leading European financial organization. She is the cofounder and ESG expert of a company that provides ESG assessment and consultancy on improvement and reporting. Previously, she worked in mergers and acquisitions, post-merger integration, and intercultural communication at multinational companies. She is a polyglot and holds a master's degree in international business from a Swiss university.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/4600ebaa-9608-4885-ae23-5ad6f582576b-8f0f58a8-2232-46a9-be3a-7f57d8410f5a.png", "full_name": "Özge O.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1095631, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1095627, "description": "Understanding and selecting among different ESG investment approaches and strategies", "preview": false }, { "id": 1095628, "description": "Choosing the right ESG strategy for different asset classes", "preview": false }, { "id": 1095629, "description": "Embedding ESG across the investment process chain", "preview": false }, { "id": 1095630, "description": "Company analysis and valuation through an ESG lens", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 887340, "text": "

You are an asset manager at a mid-sized fund that has traditionally invested in diverse industries, including oil and gas. In a recent internal meeting, senior management asked all asset managers to improve the overall ESG performance of their funds. The asset owners want a better ESG performance but have little tolerance for reduced returns on investment.


How would you implement the directive to improve the ESG performance of your portfolio while balancing the need to maintain financial returns?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7916717, "text": "

Immediately move out of all fossil fuel investments. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916718, "text": "

Move out of a small amount of fossil fuel investments, and use the released amount to invest in carbon capture technologies.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916719, "text": "

Stay in certain oil and gas companies if they have a net-zero transition plan aligned with 2050 goals.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916720, "text": "

Stay in certain oil and gas companies if their green transition is running, and use the released amount to invest in innovative solar batteries.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1095631, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 887340, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 887341, "text": "

You are an investment consultant for a global institutional investor. Major shareholders are unhappy with their investments in “sin industries” due to a misalignment of values. By the end of the current financial year, the shareholders want to maintain a well-distributed risk level with a positive return on investment. If possible, they prefer investing in companies with a balanced board gender ratio and a strong commitment to reducing greenhouse gas emissions.


How should you proceed with these ESG investment objectives in mind?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7916721, "text": "

Divest from the “sin stocks” and continue investing in companies with balanced board gender ratios.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916722, "text": "

Divest from the “sin stocks” and invest in several more companies that have a balanced board gender ratio and a 2030 net-zero target.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916723, "text": "

Keep the existing “sin stocks” and increase engagement and voting activities in those companies.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916724, "text": "

Divest from the “sin stocks” and invest in companies that benefit commercially from the trend of sustainable products/services.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1095631, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 887341, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 887342, "text": "

Veganism involves avoiding animal products or animal testing in food, clothes, and consumer goods.


What metrics should you research to assess the potential economic impact of this trend on your portfolio companies?

Greenhouse gas emissions of meat producers

Stock prices of food and beverage and luxury textile companies

Sustainability reports of dairy manufacturers

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1095631, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 887342, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 887343, "text": "

You are an analyst at a private equity firm. For the next investment round, your manager has shortlisted some companies from the same sector and industry. Your task is to compare and evaluate these companies based on their ESG materiality perception and reporting practices.


Which of the following sources should you review to best assess their ESG performance?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7916729, "text": "

The Sustainability Accounting Standards Board (SASB) aligned version of their sustainability reports.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916730, "text": "

The Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) aligned version of their sustainability reports.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7916731, "text": "

Net-zero plans and targets for the year 2030.

{ "id": 923263, "name": "Decentralized Finance (DeFi)", "summary": "This Decentralized Finance (DeFi) test evaluates candidates’ technical knowledge of DeFi and the DeFi ecosystem. You want a candidate who can avoid common pitfalls and navigate popular sensationalism to lead your efforts in this exciting and sometimes tumultuous space. \n\nThis Decentralized Finance test assesses candidates’ knowledge of the core technologies, problems, and use cases of the modern DeFi ecosystem. Through questions that focus on awareness of popular tools, platforms, investment strategies, and security best practices, it evaluates a wide range of skills. These include candidates’ abilities to plan, create, and manage DeFi funds, contracts, and apps.\n\nCandidates who perform well on this test will have a strong grasp of DeFi and practical experience working in this space. They know how to work with popular protocols and platforms to maximize profits and mitigate losses. This test will help you find candidates who possess the technical skills needed to steward your company’s crypto funds and move forward in this ever-changing niche.", "relevant": "DeFi engineers, blockchain engineers, DeFi investors, smart contract auditors, smart contract engineers", "job_roles": [ 1979 ], "owner": { "id": 479027, "biography": "Jes got into tech during his time in the Mexican military and fell in love with software. { "id": 894842, "name": "Costing of Products and Services", "summary": "This Costing of Products and Services test evaluates candidates’ ability to calculate the cost of goods sold, services rendered, and activities performed. This test will help you hire candidates who can accurately compute your business costs.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Business profits are inversely correlated with. Due to the impact of the costs of goods solds, services rendered, and activities performed on the bottom line of a business, costing is of significantly high importance across all business entities. Costing not only results in determination of cost and profits, but it also plays a crucial role in various business decisions, including the final pricing of goods and services, and decisions related to in-house production versus outsourcing. Hiring a costing expert will help your business make sense of financial data, including inventory and labor costs, to help you uncover inefficiencies and make your business even more profitable. \n\nThis test assesses candidates’ costing skills and their ability to accurately compute total and per unit cost of goods sold, services rendered, and activities performed. This test covers candidates’ knowledge of different costing systems and cost accumulation. It also examines candidates’ ability to plan and control costs, and to analyze costs and profits. Finally, this test evaluates candidates’ ability to budget and standardize costs.\n\nThis Costing of Goods and Services will help you hire candidates who possess the skills required to accurately cost your goods and services and help you make business decisions in line with improving your bottom line.", "relevant": "Cost analysts, cost estimators, pricing specialists, and any other roles requiring an intermediate knowledge of costing of goods and services.", "job_roles": [ 3358, 1565, 2438, 4870 ], "owner": { "id": 464765, "biography": "Abdul is a chartered accountant with over 15 years of experience managing other accountants and staff in many businesses, large and small. Abdul also has an MBA with significant consulting experience across business sectors, including oil and gas, pharmaceuticals, food, and education. He has worked as a university lecturer in accounting, finance, and tax-related subjects for more than five years and currently works on complex risk management policies as a senior risk management officer.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/8ac7b8ba-233e-4bb8-9f16-a89a8cb28aee-eba532b2-dc00-4590-b0b3-9d7f472ca15b.png", "full_name": "Abdul G.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 927026, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 927022, "description": "Costing systems and cost accumulation", "preview": false }, { "id": 927023, "description": "Planning and controlling costs", "preview": false }, { "id": 927024, "description": "Analyzing costs and profits", "preview": false }, { "id": 927025, "description": "Budgeting and standardizing costing", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 614162, "text": "

What is the marginal costing profit?

{ "id": 837474, "name": "QuickBooks Online (UK Version)", "summary": "This QuickBooks Online test evaluates candidates’ proficiency in the UK version of the software, including their ability to navigate, process transactions, maintain lists, generate reports, prepare reconciliations, and other key accounting functions.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "QuickBooks Online is an accounting software package that is geared mainly toward small and medium-sized businesses for the processing of accounting information, paying bills, generating sales invoices, preparing reconciliations, and running reports to manage the financial aspect of the business.\n\nThis QuickBooks Online test evaluates candidates’ ability to use the software in four key areas: set up a company and maintain lists such as the Chart of Accounts, customers, and suppliers; process sales transactions, set up products and services, and process customer payments and refunds; process supplier purchases and expenses, bill payments, and refunds; and set up the banking function and prepare bank reconciliations and other accounting functions such as processing journal entries and running reports as required by the core functions.\n\nCandidates who perform well on this test have a strong grasp of QuickBooks Online and possess practical experience using the software. They have a good understanding of how to navigate the system and process accounting transactions, know which reports to run for a core business function, and can prepare reconciliations to ensure the company’s financial data is accurate.\n\nThis test does not cover taxes in QuickBooks Online, as that process and requirements are different from country to country.", "relevant": "Bookkeepers, accountants, financial clerks, financial managers, and business and clerical administrators.", "job_roles": [ 1883, 1886, 1463, 1949, 1985, 1499, 1502, 2036, 1577, 2426, 2429, 2432, 2435, 2438, 1616, 1619, 4383, 2441, 2471, 3997, 3636, 3998, 5138, 3065 ], "owner": { "id": 82123, "biography": "A Chartered Accountant with a Masters of Commerce Degree, Mary-Ann has been involved in all aspects of business, finance, accounting, taxation (both compliance and international), as well as financial systems, procedures, and designing and implementing internal controls over 20 years. Her interests include business and economic news, monitoring stock markets, and reading both technical material and fiction novels.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/68f88d5d-f4a6-4f0f-bcfb-08ae7087b134-ad99571b-eabb-4fbb-afc8-eddb63c9f382.png", "full_name": "Mary-Ann de W.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 867851, "description": "Preview Questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 867852, "description": "Setup and maintenance", "preview": false }, { "id": 867853, "description": "Invoicing and sales", "preview": false }, { "id": 867854, "description": "Expenses and suppliers", "preview": false }, { "id": 867855, "description": "Banking and accounting functions", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 586848, "text": "

{ "id": 536780, "name": "Purchase Executive (Local Procurement)", "summary": "This Purchase Executive test evaluates a candidate’s ability to procure locally sourced materials and services. This screening test will help you hire purchase executives who can execute and complete the full procure-to-pay (P2P) cycle.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "A great purchase executive can help you achieve business savings by helping you choose suppliers with the best prices and terms. They can identify the goods and services that are crucial to your company and take appropriate steps to secure your supply chains by diversifying supply. \n\nThis Purchase Executive test evaluates a candidate’s ability to plan and place orders, ensure on-time-in-full (OTIF) delivery of goods, onboard and manage suppliers, and handle price changes and other commercial issues that may arise.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify purchase executives who can procure locally sourced materials and services, executing a complete procure-to-pay (P2P) cycle. Candidates who do well on this test will have 1-2 years of experience in procurement and be able to plan sourcing, place orders, arrange logistics, and handle various commercial issues. Successful candidates will be able to understand price escalations and benchmark prices along various suppliers. They will be capable of assisting the strategic sourcing department in supplier onboarding.", "relevant": "This screening test is relevant for purchase managers and executives, procurement specialists, buyers, people in supply chain roles, or any job roles that require knowledge of local purchasing.", "job_roles": [ 2000, 2810, 2855, 1751, 3041, 3044 ], "owner": { "id": 264458, "biography": "A startup founder with over 16 years of experience in the automobile, IT, and renewable energy sectors, Bhupendra has an MBA in International Business & Supply Chain Management, and has consulted on projects for the Skill India program. Bhupendra’s areas of expertise include supply chain management, warehousing, logistics, and automation. \n\nBhupendra lives in Noida, India, with his wife Dipali and his two adorable children, Tanvi and Kavya.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/61caa4ec-0e64-4454-8cf5-200eb386968d-4129793a-238a-4f95-83ee-dd980439fbf6.png", "full_name": "Bhupendra K.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 558759, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 558755, "description": "Planning & ordering", "preview": false }, { "id": 558756, "description": "Ensuring OTIF delivery & follow-up", "preview": false }, { "id": 558757, "description": "Onboarding & managing suppliers", "preview": false }, { "id": 558758, "description": "Handling pricing & commercial issues", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 357106, "text": "

You have to place orders for the next month. The manufacturing resources planning (MRP) run wasn’t successfully completed, and a few purchase requisitions (PRs) may not be available in the enterprise resource planning (ERP) system. You will consider the store’s stock, goods in transit (GIT), and PRs available in the ERP before requesting an MRP run for the quantity you are short.

 

How many additional PRs are required for the seating system?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": false, "answers": [ { "id": 5166729, "text": "

200

300

500

{ "id": 673813, "name": "Accounting Terminology (US)", "summary": "This hiring test evaluates candidates’ practical skills in understanding various accounting terms related to financial statements, books of accounts, and other aspects of financial transactions. This screening test focuses on terms used in the US.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Every profession has its own terminologies and jargon that help convey a large volume of information and other relevant details through a very small statement or even a single word.\n\nThe accounting profession also has a large number of unique terminologies. These terminologies are used to describe financial information and related processes. Financial information can incorporate lots of different things: the right to receive an amount from another person; the obligation to pay an amount to another person; how much you have earned or lost or expended during a certain period; or the total worth of a business entity or a particular thing. Accountants use terms and phrases to quickly communicate the meaning of financial information, and this hiring test focuses on these terms.\n\nCandidates who perform well on the test are likely to possess a good understanding of key accounting terminologies used in the United States.
