{
    "id": 494,
    "name": "Big 5 (OCEAN)",
    "summary": "The big 5 personality test follows the Five-Factor Model, an empirical-based theory in psychology that evaluates five overarching dimensions of personality: openness, conscientiousness, extroversion, agreeableness, and emotional stability.",
    "duration": 600.0,
    "estimated_duration": 600.0,
    "type": [
        {
            "id": 2,
            "name": "Personality & culture",
            "visible": false
        }
    ],
    "is_new": false,
    "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test",
    "default_language": "en",
    "description": "The big 5 personality test is based on the five-factor model (FFM) theory that posits five broad trait dimensions or domains as the basis of different personalities. The model has been shaped by the work of various researchers over three decades (from the 1960s to the 1990s) who analyzed verbal descriptors of human behavior. Eventually, the long lists of traits proposed in the complicated models of early research were organized at the highest level into five overarching factors that affect a person’s personality. \n\nEach factor is measured as a spectrum: openness to experience ranges from inventive and curious to consistent and cautious, conscientiousness ranges from efficient and organized to extravagant and careless, extraversion ranges from outgoing and energetic to solitary and reserved, agreeableness ranges from friendly and compassionate to challenging and callous, and neuroticism ranges from sensitive and nervous to resilient and confident. \n\nThe big 5 test leads test-takers on a self-evaluation of their behavior by asking them to score various statements on a scale from 1 (very inaccurate) to 5 (very accurate). The score candidates provide for each statement places them on one of five possible positions on the spectrum of each factor. The nature of the test structure is best suited to evaluating the compositions and dynamics of existing teams for learning and development and growth purposes, rather than for candidates applying to join teams.\n\nThe results provide insights into the test-taker's position on each factor and describe the personality traits that characterize their behavior. They also provide insight into their strengths and opportunities for improvement, and how they relate to others.",
    "relevant": "All job roles. The big 5 test should not be used for hiring decisions, but as a tool to gain a deeper understanding of test-takers' personality inclinations. The insights into personality traits can help enrich learning and development conversations.",

He has also shared his skills and knowledge with a broad audience by authoring e-learning courses and books on negotiation techniques in several languages.", "country": 64, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/2bf7dd4d-a324-4708-bfa2-4002c14f2078-8ce75c2b-2b96-4a9e-a679-9f3ee780560c.jpeg", "full_name": "Alexis K.", "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexis-kyprianou-43a61b3/" }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1371704, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1371705, "description": "Controlling and driving the discussion", "preview": false }, { "id": 1371706, "description": "Influencing the counterparty", "preview": false }, { "id": 1371707, "description": "Leveraging the psychology of the counterparty", "preview": false }, { "id": 1371708, "description": "Using emotional intelligence", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 1171602, "text": "

You work for a plastics manufacturing company and are negotiating with supplier X to sell you dye. Supplier X has the best dyes, but supplier Y also sells dye, though of a slightly lower quality. If you cannot negotiate a suitable price with supplier X, you are prepared to get your dye from supplier Y.

 

Which of the following strategies is most likely to help you get the best price from supplier X?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9771940, "text": "

Discuss tentatively with supplier Y to see what price they can offer before starting your discussions with supplier X.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771941, "text": "

Initiate discussions with suppliers X and Y at the same time.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771942, "text": "

Initiate discussions with supplier X and start a negotiation with supplier Y if you cannot negotiate the price you need.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771943, "text": "

Tell supplier X at the beginning of discussions that you are considering purchasing from supplier Y.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1371704, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 51, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 615369, "identifier": "Q00.051", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 615369, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 4 }, { "id": 1171603, "text": "

You are in the middle of a negotiation with a customer to get a large maintenance contract for their numerous air-conditioning units. You need to get a contract with this customer because you are well below your targets. However, your counterparty has just made an aggressive demand and is waiting for you to respond to it.

 

What is the best way to move forward?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9771948, "text": "

State that you are going to take a break without explaining why. State when you will come back.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771949, "text": "

State that you are going to take a break without explaining why. Do not state when you will come back.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771950, "text": "

State that you are going to take a break to think about your counterparty’s demand. State when you will come back.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771951, "text": "

State that you are going to take a break to think about your counterparty’s demand. Do not state when you will come back.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1371704, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 53, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 615372, "identifier": "Q00.053", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 615372, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 4 }, { "id": 1171605, "text": "

You are negotiating a commercial contract with a prospective customer. They have just stated that your named competitor offers better contractual terms and that you should make an effort to offer terms similar to your competitor’s. You doubt that your competitor has offered terms significantly better and believe that your prospective customer is bluffing so that you will offer a better deal.

 

How should you respond to the prospective customer?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9771952, "text": "

“I doubt our competitor is offering you better overall value.”

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771953, "text": "

“What is our competitor offering you?”

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771954, "text": "

“What can you get with us that you can’t get from our competitor?”

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9771955, "text": "

“Since you are here, there is something that interests you in our offer.”

{ "id": 39438, "name": "Leadership and People Management", "summary": "The Leadership and People Management test evaluates a candidate’s ability to lead others within an organization using both influence and guidance. This test will help you hire leaders who can support and develop others to help your organization grow.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 5, "name": "Situational judgment", "visible": true }, { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Powerful leaders scale your organization’s potential. They carry out impactful strategies and provide actionable directives that get results. \n\nThis Leadership and People Management test evaluates candidates’ abilities to delegate authority and task responsibility, plan and support the development of others, provide timely guidance and feedback, and gain acceptance of ideas and plans. Rather than proposing a specific leadership style, this test follows the situational theory of leadership developed by Blanchard and Hersey and asks candidates to evaluate factors to decide when to tell, sell, participate, or delegate in different scenarios based on the needs of each situation.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify leaders who have a genuine interest in developing others and can unite talent behind important objectives. These are the leaders who understand how to align the needs and goals of the organization with the skills and aspirations of their team members to produce results and satisfaction at all levels. Successful leaders lead by example and create a space where people can share ideas, ask questions, and be accountable for their actions.", "relevant": "Managers, team leaders, and employees in other leadership roles.", "job_roles": [ 1874, 1877, 1880, 1886, 1928, 1934, 1943, 1946, 1973, 1976, 1982, 1790, 1994, 1997, 2012, 2015, 2018, 2021, 2033, 2036, 2039, 2042, 2045, 2084, 2102, 2105, 2114, 2129, 1538, 2147, 1559, 2168, 2204, 2240, 2243, 1805, 2255, 2276, 2312, 2324, 2348, 2366, 2390, 2393, 2396, 2399, 2405, 2414, 2426, 2432, 1619, 2441, 1634, 2471, 2477, 2480, 2498, 2507, 2510, 2513, 2516, 2519, 2522, 2525, 2528, 2531, 2534, 2537, 2540, 2543, 2561, 1652, 2570, 2594, 2615, 2621, 2636, 2669, 2684, 2687, 2699, 2711, 2717, 2744, 2747, 2750, 2753, 2756, 2759, 2765, 2774, 2795, 2801, 2807, 2810, 2816, 2822, 2825, 2828, 2840, 2843, 2852, 1748, 1751, 2870, 2879, 2912, 2915, 2969, 3044, 3050, 3056, 3077, 3080, 3086, 3089, 3131, 3143 ], "owner": { "id": 53, "biography": "Erika has been coaching team leaders, managers, and executives at companies of all sizes for over 10 years. A certified leadership and executive coach, Erika loves guiding the professionals she works with to explore their full leadership potential and equips with the strategies and tactics they need to lead and elevate others to do their best work. \n\nBefore turning to coaching full time, Erika started and led HR departments at various companies and built their learning and development programs.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/68bf196b-d98e-4b75-8e01-d32cae66288a-ca10cedf-2440-4b84-bdee-44f01932ce58.jpeg", "full_name": "Erika R.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 43316, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 43317, "description": "Delegate authority and task responsibility", "preview": false }, { "id": 43318, "description": "Plan and support the development of others", "preview": false }, { "id": 43319, "description": "Provide timely guidance and feedback", "preview": false }, { "id": 43320, "description": "Gain acceptance of ideas and plans", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 56500, "text": "

An employee from another department will join your team next week. They requested the transfer because they felt their work was becoming predictable and monotonous. Their performance reports show they have made good contributions to programming projects but need to improve their presentation skills.

How would you support their development?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 679811, "text": "

Discuss your team’s upcoming projects with them and trust that they will learn to create better presentations on the job.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679812, "text": "

Meet with their former manager to discuss their weaknesses and the development plan they were working on.

", "score": 1, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679813, "text": "

Meet with them to discuss their goals and training needs and set a development program together.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679814, "text": "

Research how to improve presentation skills and give them educational materials they can read to improve.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 43316, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2054183, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 56500, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 3 }, { "id": 56501, "text": "

You are in the middle of the company’s peak business period and have noticed that your team’s morale is dropping due to pressure. One of the long-term clients of the company has complained that the report your team sent last week was full of typos and inconsistent information. 


How should you approach your team about this?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 679815, "text": "

Share the client’s feedback with your team and brainstorm ways to manage the pressure of the peak period. Ask them to redo the report by next week.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679816, "text": "

Ask your team to redo the report as soon as possible. Explain that you’re not in a position to lose an important client.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679817, "text": "

Tell your team the client changed his mind and wants a revised report to avoid harming your team’s morale further with negative feedback.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679818, "text": "

Ask your team to redo the report immediately, letting them know you’re concerned about their performance and will apply disciplinary actions if it doesn’t improve.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 43316, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2054184, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 56501, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 3 }, { "id": 56502, "text": "

One of your direct reports is not making the expected progress on an assignment you have given them. When you ask them about it, they say they are feeling stressed. They are a competent worker and you know they have the skills required to complete the assignment.


How would you approach the situation?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 679819, "text": "

Remind them that they have the skills required and that you trust them to complete the work on time.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679820, "text": "

Remind them of the deadline and explain that it is not negotiable.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679821, "text": "

Discuss what’s causing their stress and discuss ways to mitigate it with a time-bound plan.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679822, "text": "

Outline what they still need to do for the project, give them an action plan, and check in on their progress daily.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 43316, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 5, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2054185, "identifier": "Q00.005", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 56502, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 3 }, { "id": 56503, "text": "

As the Director of Human Resources, you have noticed stark differences between the leadership styles of top and middle managers at your company. You want to implement a leadership development program to harmonize the company’s approach to leadership. The CEO of the company, however, does not think this is a critical issue that needs addressing at the moment.


How can you convince the CEO to approve the program?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 679823, "text": "

Wait until the stark differences in leadership styles affect a key metric in a demonstrable way, then pitch the program to the CEO again.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679824, "text": "

Write a report explaining all the differences you see in leadership styles and give examples of what a harmonized leadership style would look like.

", "score": 3, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679825, "text": "

Explain your idea to other directors in your company and ask that they support you in your request for approval from the CEO.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 679826, "text": "

Write a report on the positive impact a harmonized leadership style would have on the company’s bottom line.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 43316, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 6, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": true, "duration": 0, "previous_version": 2054186, "identifier": "Q00.006", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 56503, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 3 } ], "get_level_display": "Intermediate", "preview": 43316, "modified": "2024-12-09T20:21:19.398907Z", "test_uuid": "15800955-aa07-41ce-83a8-f56564c20500", "is_premium": true, "is_private_test": false, "is_spreadsheet_test": false, "test_type_names": [ "Situational judgment", "Role-specific skills" ], "available_languages": [ "en", "es", "nl", "it-it", "ja-jp", "pt-br" ], "is_language_agnostic_test": false, "programming_languages": [], "status": "published", "is_coderunner_v1": null }

{ "id": 1372827, "name": "Digital Agility", "summary": "This Digital Agility test is meant to evaluate a candidate’s ability to navigate digital challenges. This screening test helps you hire professionals who can adapt to any situation in a fast-paced digital world.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 5, "name": "Situational judgment", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today’s ever-evolving digital landscape, the ability to navigate and thrive in dynamic environments is crucial for businesses to maintain their competitive edge. Individuals with strong digital agility can help your business embrace new technologies, streamline processes, and drive growth. \n\nThis Digital Agility test evaluates candidates' skills in strategic technology adoption as well as decision-making and problem-solving in digital environments. It also assesses digital change leadership and cross-functional collaboration skills. \n\nThis test will help you identify individuals who will thrive in leadership roles that demand a high level of digital agility to drive business results, whether by streamlining operations, enhancing decision-making processes, or driving innovation across teams. Candidates who perform well on this test are equipped to not only keep your organization digitally relevant but also to capitalize on new opportunities that arise in the ever-shifting digital landscape.", "relevant": "Project managers, IT managers, operations managers, product managers, growth managers, team leads, and other leadership roles that require a high level of digital agility.", "job_roles": [ 4180, 2342, 2498, 3541, 4646, 6308, 2843, 5158 ], "owner": { "id": 719152, "biography": "TestGorilla's IP Development and Science & Innovation CoEs are responsible for delivering leading-edge, science-based assessment content, insights, and innovation. Collectively, they boast more than 15 advanced degrees, over 100 scientific publications and presentations, and almost 100 years of assessment and talent acquisition industry experience.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/063647b9-ee9f-4fbb-926b-311da36920e8-23490e3b-f991-43cb-9989-b6932af4054d.jpeg", "full_name": "IP & Science Centers of Expertise (CoEs)", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1420205, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1420201, "description": "Strategic technology adoption", "preview": false }, { "id": 1420202, "description": "Decision-making and problem-solving", "preview": false }, { "id": 1420203, "description": "Digital change leadership", "preview": false }, { "id": 1420204, "description": "Cross-functional collaboration for digital innovation", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 1210976, "text": "

You are a senior manager in a large retail company, and you are responsible for improving customer experience and increasing online sales. You are tasked with implementing a new digital strategy that includes integrating new technologies into the existing infrastructure and aligning with the overall business goals.


What should be your first step?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10102545, "text": "

Conduct a thorough review of the current technological landscape to identify any gaps.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102546, "text": "

Engage with key stakeholders across different departments to gather their insights and input.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102547, "text": "

Set clear objectives and key performance indicators (KPIs) for the digital strategy.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102548, "text": "

Evaluate potential risks and challenges associated with implementing new technologies.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1420205, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1210976, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1210977, "text": "

You are a project manager at a software development company. You are tasked with managing multiple projects simultaneously, with tight deadlines and limited resources. One project involves developing a new mobile app, while another involves enhancing an existing software product. Both projects require immediate attention and are equally important to the company's success.


Which action should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10102549, "text": "

Request additional resources from senior management to handle both projects simultaneously.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102550, "text": "

Delegate tasks to your team members based on their skills and expertise.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102551, "text": "

Assign one project to a senior team member and handle the other one yourself.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102552, "text": "

Request for an extension of deadlines from both clients to manage the workload.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1420205, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1210977, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1210978, "text": "

Which action should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10102553, "text": "

Assign a dedicated team member to each department to serve as a point person for questions and support.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102554, "text": "

Set up regular check-in meetings with each team to review their progress and address any challenges.

", "score": 3, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102555, "text": "

Organize additional training sessions on how to use the project management tool.

", "score": 4, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102556, "text": "

Create a user-friendly guide or manual that outlines best practices for monitoring progress using the project management tool.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1420205, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": true, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1210978, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1210980, "text": "

Which action should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10102561, "text": "

Schedule a one-on-one meeting with the team member to discuss their progress and any challenges they may be facing.

Request that the team member provide daily progress reports until their tasks are back on track.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102563, "text": "

Implement a mandatory daily reporting system for all team members.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10102564, "text": "

{ "id": 1310654, "name": "Design Thinking", "summary": "This Design Thinking test evaluates candidates' skills in user-centric problem-solving, fostering innovation that enhances business competitiveness. It helps you hire design thinking experts who drive user satisfaction through creative solutions.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today's business landscape, design thinking is an invaluable asset, fostering user-centricity, innovation, and effective problem-solving. By embracing this approach, organizations gain a deep understanding of user needs, resulting in elevated satisfaction and loyalty. Design thinking ignites creative exploration, stimulating novel solutions vital for staying competitive.\n\nThis Design Thinking test comprehensively evaluates candidates across four critical skill areas: Empathy & User-Centered Focus, Problem Framing & Definition, Ideation & Creativity, and Prototyping & Iteration.\n\nCandidates excelling in this screening test will demonstrate proficiency in design thinking methodologies, equipping your business to innovate and excel in the market. He holds a master's degree in strategic design from Delft University of Technology.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/264392bb-a8fe-42c6-b53b-d57ad2f74580-b9667983-e3d4-4fe8-9406-21542e6af87c.png", "full_name": "Yee Jek K.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1356705, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1356701, "description": "Empathy & User-Centered Focus", "preview": false }, { "id": 1356702, "description": "Problem Framing & Definition", "preview": false }, { "id": 1356703, "description": "Ideation & Creativity", "preview": false }, { "id": 1356704, "description": "Prototyping & Iteration", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 1158845, "text": "

You have been hired as a product development manager at a company that specializes in developing camera accessories. The company is looking to expand its product line, and you have been tasked with brainstorming new ideas. Due to privacy concerns, access to customer data is limited.


What would be the most effective method to gather insights on customer needs and preferences? 


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 9674883, "text": "

Organize a focus group with photographers to discuss their accessory usage.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9674884, "text": "

Examine online product reviews of competing camera accessories.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 9674885, "text": "

Analyze advertisements related to photography on major social media platforms.

What is the best way to demonstrate empathy for your colleague?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8937435, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937437, "text": "

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8937438, "text": "

The employee further shared that their friend is trustworthy, and they are confident the friend will maintain confidentiality. The employee seeks your advice regarding the most appropriate response per company policy.


What should you suggest?


", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12676652, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676654, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676655, "text": "

Making this change would immediately lead to an increase in reported profitability. 


Before giving your consent, what are some of the ethical factors you should keep in mind?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12676656, "text": "

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676658, "text": "

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676659, "text": "

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676660, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12676661, "text": "

Do you need to announce this change, or can you go ahead and do this immediately?

Collectively, they boast more than 15 advanced degrees, over 100 scientific publications and presentations, and almost 100 years of assessment and talent acquisition industry experience.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/4ef40767-eac7-4023-b3d3-023abd9212b9-8e2ad74e-2a13-4f0d-a708-cd945bc4386a.jpeg", "full_name": "IP & Science Centers of Expertise (CoEs)", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1786040, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1786036, "description": "Performance appraisal", "preview": false }, { "id": 1786037, "description": "Giving feedback", "preview": false }, { "id": 1786038, "description": "Managing performance", "preview": false }, { "id": 1786039, "description": "Fairness in performance management", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 1428064, "text": "

You are a retail store manager specializing in mattresses and want to set performance goals with your sales team for the upcoming quarter. You aim to motivate them with challenging yet attainable targets.


What is an effective stretch goal to set with a sales team member?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12481336, "text": "

Increase sales of foam mattresses by 10%. 

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481337, "text": "

Increase the number of outbound phone calls made. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481338, "text": "

Increase sales of foam mattresses by 75%. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481339, "text": "

Increase the number of hours spent listening to sales podcasts. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1786040, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1428064, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1428065, "text": "

You are a human resources manager at a manufacturing company. You are working with a manager to evaluate the employee appraisal process for machine operators. The manager explains that the most important criterion for being a good machine operator is reliability. They want to base the majority of the performance appraisal on traits, such as the machine operator’s dependability. 


How would you respond to the manager?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12481340, "text": "

Agree with the manager’s suggestion and develop a trait appraisal that allows managers to assess a machine operator’s dependability. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481341, "text": "

Develop a 10-factor forced choice appraisal method in which one factor is the machine operator's dependability.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481342, "text": "

Ask for behavioral examples of dependability to integrate into a behavioral appraisal.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481343, "text": "

Develop a forced distribution system in which the manager rank-orders employees based on their dependability traits. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1786040, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1428065, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1428066, "text": "

You are a team leader at a marketing agency. One of your team members is responsible for creating social media content. Recently, you’ve noticed that they often seem distracted during team meetings, and the quality of their work has declined. Their social media posts are creative, but they often contain inaccuracies. You suspect that they are not applying the team’s fact-checking procedures.  


How should you approach giving feedback to this team member?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12481344, "text": "

Ask the full team to assess this team member’s most recent social media posts during a team meeting, using it as a learning activity for all. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481345, "text": "

Provide general feedback to the whole team about the need to be engaged in team meetings and to use the fact-checking procedures. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481346, "text": "

Privately ask this team member about the performance issues, inquiring about why they have seemed so distracted recently. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481347, "text": "

Privately explain the performance issues and ask them to start documenting their fact-checking procedures.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1786040, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1428066, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1428067, "text": "

You are a manager at a software development company. In a recent employee opinion survey, employees complained that their annual appraisals did not reflect their overall performance and focused too much on their final quarter productivity. 


Which of the following steps could you take to avoid recency bias in this year’s review?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 12481348, "text": "

Meet with employees one-on-one to discuss their performance in the final quarter, seeking ways to improve for the next quarter. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481349, "text": "

Meet with other managers to calibrate performance appraisal ratings, ensuring that your ratings align with those of other managers. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481350, "text": "

Assess the performance appraisal ratings across your team for potential bias, identifying differences based on characteristics, such as gender.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 12481351, "text": "

Maintain a log of each employee’s key contributions and performance, updating it throughout each quarter. 

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1786040, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 4, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.004", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1428067, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 } ], "get_level_display": "Intermediate", "preview": 1786040, "modified": "2024-02-16T11:49:36.860500Z", "test_uuid": "1da17108-9cd6-4f88-bd87-3dece693dee1", "is_premium": true, "is_private_test": false, "is_spreadsheet_test": false, "test_type_names": [ "Role-specific skills" ], "available_languages": [ "en" ], "is_language_agnostic_test": false, "programming_languages": [], "status": "published", "is_coderunner_v1": null }

What should be your first course of action?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10923106, "text": "

Buy a wide range of dresses in different styles and sizes.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923107, "text": "

Analyze the customer feedback to pinpoint which styles, colors, or sizes of dresses are requested.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923108, "text": "

Carry out a survey to gather additional feedback on specific styles of dresses customers would like to see.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923109, "text": "

Implement a discount strategy on existing dresses to draw in customers.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1545259, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1295197, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1295208, "text": "

Which actions should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10923358, "text": "

Include as many items of the collection as possible in the four displays.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923359, "text": "

Integrate the new collection with current collections in four existing displays.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923360, "text": "

Delegate each of the four displays to a different sales associate to create.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923361, "text": "

Display the collection in four high-traffic areas of the store.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923362, "text": "

Create the four displays around a single unifying theme.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 10923363, "text": "

Place all items in the four displays at the same height and depth.

{ "id": 1107911, "name": "Natural Language Processing (NLP)", "summary": "This Natural Language Processing (NLP) evaluates candidates’ technical knowledge and their ability to solve situational tasks in, NLP. The test will help identify developers who are proficient in NLP.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In today's world, Natural Language Processing (NLP) has become an essential tool for processing and understanding vast amounts of textual data. It is a field of study that combines the power of computer science and linguistics to create applications that can analyze and interpret human language.\n\nOur NLP test evaluates candidates’ knowledge of the essential concepts in NLP, covering topics such as the NLP pipeline, text representation and classification, information extraction, chatbots, and topic modeling. The questions on this test focus on different scenarios when working with textual data, covering the different NLP functionalities for dealing with each of them.\n\nCandidates who perform well on the test have a strong understanding of core NLP approaches and can make the best use of these approaches when working with different types of textual data. They have all the necessary skills to help your business harness the power of NLP to gain insights into customer needs, improve business operations, and make data-driven decisions. Whether you are looking to build chatbots, perform sentiment analysis, or extract information from text, our NLP test will help you identify the right candidates for the job.", "relevant": "NLP engineers, machine-learning engineers,\nartificial intelligence engineers, data analysts, and any other roles requiring intermediate knowledge of NLP.", "job_roles": [ 2279, 2282, 3375, 1592, 2510, 4678, 2648, 2651 ], "owner": { "id": 583561, "biography": "Gary has been working in the data science field for more than three years and is proficient in the fields of machine learning and data analysis. { "id": 1210659, "name": "Machine Learning in Amazon Web Services (AWS)", "summary": "This Machine Learning in AWS test evaluates candidates' ability to design and manage ML systems on AWS. It covers key areas such as AWS infrastructure for machine learning, model development and deployment, monitoring and optimization, and AWS machine learning low-code and no-code services.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify talented individuals who possess a solid understanding of ML engineering procedures and can effectively apply them in various data scenarios using AWS services. Candidates who excel in this test will show the ability to drive ML initiatives, optimize ML models, and leverage AWS infrastructure to achieve business objectives. Hiring such skilled professionals will enhance your organization's capabilities, accelerate innovation, and help you gain a competitive edge in the era of machine learning.\n\nBy utilizing this Machine Learning in AWS test, you can confidently assess candidates' expertise in ML on the AWS platform. With skilled ML practitioners adept at leveraging AWS services, you can unlock the full potential of your data, build intelligent applications, and drive data-powered innovation throughout your organization.", "relevant": "Machine learning engineers, data scientists, MLOpps engineers, and cloud architects.", "job_roles": [ 2084, 2099, 1592, 2510, 2648, 2651 ], "owner": { "id": 647848, "biography": "Gary has been working in the data science field for more than three years and is proficient in the fields of machine learning and data analysis. { "id": 968822, "name": "TensorFlow", "summary": "This test evaluates candidates’ technical knowledge of TensorFlow. The test will help identify developers who are proficient in TensorFlow and are capable of implementing various deep-learning models with that framework.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 7, "name": "Programming skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "TensorFlow is an open-source machine-learning library for Python, developed and maintained by the Google Brain team. It is widely used for developing and training deep-learning models and is designed to be easy to use and flexible, with a focus on providing strong support for training and inference on graphical processing units (GPUs). TensorFlow makes it easy to implement complex models, such as those with branching or loops, and it also makes it easier to debug and optimize TensorFlow code. It also includes many high-level libraries and tools for tasks such as natural language processing and computer vision, as well as a number of pre-trained models that can be fine-tuned for a variety of tasks.\n\nHiring someone experienced with TensorFlow can help your business build and train deep-learning models more quickly and efficiently, reducing the time and resources required to develop machine-learning-based solutions. An experienced TensorFlow developer will know how to design and train deep-learning models that achieve good performance and help to improve the accuracy and effectiveness of a machine-learning system. TensorFlow's dynamic computational graph allows for greater flexibility in model design and training, making it easier to adapt machine-learning systems to new tasks or changing requirements or to integrate them with other tools and platforms.\n\nThis test covers the fundamentals of TensorFlow, advanced TensorFlow functionalities, and working with convolutional neural network architecture and complex neural architecture in TensorFlow. Candidates who perform well on this test will have a strong grasp of core TensorFlow functionalities and be able to make the best use of each one when working with different types of models.\n\nThis test will help you hire candidates with the TensorFlow skills necessary to help your company train large or complex machine-learning systems that are easy to deploy and maintain.", "relevant": "Deep-learning engineers, machine-learning engineers, artificial intelligence engineers, data analysts, and any other roles requiring an intermediate knowledge of TensorFlow.", "job_roles": [ 2150, 2279, 2282, 1592, 2510, 2648, 2651 ], "owner": { "id": 506245, "biography": "Gary has been working in the data science field for more than three years and is proficient in the fields of machine learning and data analysis. { "id": 841154, "name": "Artificial Intelligence", "summary": "This Artificial Intelligence (AI) test evaluates candidates’ grasp of core AI concepts and their ability to solve situational AI tasks. This screening test will help you identify candidates capable of tackling a variety of business challenges using AI.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "In our current age of information and technology, all businesses have something to gain from leveraging artificial intelligence. Already, AI can support the automation of business processes, help businesses gain insights through data analysis, and engage with customers and employees. Hiring professionals with knowledge of AI can help your business save time and money by automating and optimizing tasks and processes, increasing productivity and efficiency, and leading to faster business decisions based on the outputs of cognitive technologies. In short, businesses that do not adopt artificial intelligence risk falling behind in an increasingly competitive business landscape.\n\nThis Artificial Intelligence test evaluates candidates’ knowledge of fundamental AI concepts such as local search, environments with uncertainty, games and constraint satisfaction problems, propositional and first-order logic, automated planning, and robotics. The questions on this test focus on scenarios typically encountered when working with real-life problems, allowing you to assess candidates for artificial intelligence skills that provide functionality for dealing with real business challenges by applying corresponding modeling. ", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1221195, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1023869, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1023870, "text": "

You work in-house for a company that has spent five years and over a billion dollars developing a breakthrough product. It is now time to launch the product to the market, a process that includes a large-scale public relations campaign. As the PR manager, you must work with many stakeholders in the marketing department and beyond to ensure it is a fully integrated campaign. 


What is the first action you should take to best partner with the marketing team?



", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8801568, "text": "

Prepare a final PR plan to send to Marketing, telling them to contact you if they have any questions. 

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801569, "text": "

Meet alone with the company’s CEO to get her input on the PR plan.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801570, "text": "

Devise and execute your PR plan, assuming Marketing will contact them if they have any questions or concerns.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801571, "text": "

Prepare a proposed PR plan to present to Marketing for their input.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1221195, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1023870, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 1023878, "text": "

The CEO of your company was just arrested for public intoxication at a major industry trade show. Members of the media filmed him getting arrested and then later being released from jail. The press is now calling his office for a statement. As the PR in charge, he calls you for advice on how to respond.


With the goal of minimizing reputational damage to the CEO and the company, what should you tell the CEO to do when media outlets request comments?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 8801572, "text": "

Advise that all media calls be directed to the press office (yourself) for an official statement and/or details on potential press conferences.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801573, "text": "

To take as many media calls as possible and answer all media questions as best he can off the top of his head.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801574, "text": "

To only speak to national media outlets like NBC News and the Wall Street Journal to reach the broadest publicity level.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 8801575, "text": "

To say ‘no comment’ and hang up.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1221195, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 4, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.004", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 1023878, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 } ], "get_level_display": "Intermediate", "preview": 1221195, "modified": "2023-10-31T19:57:44.602589Z", "test_uuid": "bd245ea3-0b50-485f-9a9f-eaa7e12b0aa6", "is_premium": true, "is_private_test": false, "is_spreadsheet_test": false, "test_type_names": [ "Role-specific skills" ], "available_languages": [ "en" ], "is_language_agnostic_test": false, "programming_languages": [], "status": "published", "is_coderunner_v1": null }

{ "id": 598357, "name": "B2C Growth Marketing (Ecommerce)", "summary": "This growth marketing test evaluates the depth and breadth of candidates’ multi-domain marketing knowledge and their ability to diagnose growth barriers, develop growth plans, and implement them for a B2C or an ecommerce business.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "If your organization is in a competitive market and is aiming for growth, creating a new revenue center, or is launching a new product, you will need help from a new breed of marketing professionals: growth marketers.\n\nGrowth marketers bring deep experience in multiple areas of marketing. They approach problem-solving pragmatically and possess hands-on technical skills, such as optimization, testing, and experimental design.\n\nFind out which candidate is an ultimate growth marketing machine. { "id": 990150, "name": "B2B Sales Management (Manufacturing and Software & Services)", "summary": "This B2B Sales Management test evaluates a candidate’s knowledge of key sales management areas including strategy, enablement, incentives, and territory management. This screening test will help you hire managers who can lead your sales team to success.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 6, "name": "Role-specific skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Hiring sales managers with strong skills has become more crucial than ever in the modern business landscape. As technology continues to change the way sales are made, it is essential to have leaders who can keep pace and drive results, maximizing their resources to get the most out of their sales team in the shortest time possible. By investing in sales management talent, businesses can improve their sales performance, increase customer satisfaction and retention, and drive growth.\n\nThis B2B Sales Management (Manufacturing and Software & Services) test is designed to evaluate key areas of sales leadership, including sales strategy, sales enablement, sales incentives, and territory management. The test covers essential skills such as strategic thinking, leadership, motivation, communication, and problem-solving, which are crucial for success in sales management.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify manufacturing, software, and services sales managers who can translate their skills in the covered areas into tangible business results. Candidates who perform well on this test have the potential to build and lead winning sales teams, improve sales performance, and drive growth for your business. By incorporating this test into your hiring process, you can ensure you are hiring the best sales management talent and maximizing your chances for success.", "relevant": "This screening test will help you hire sales managers, group sales managers, sales coordinators, area sales managers, inside sales managers, sales directors, international sales managers, sales commercial managers, and sales executives.", "job_roles": [ 6129, 3573, 2669, 6180, 3692, 2948, 3823 ], "owner": { "id": 518533, "biography": "Martin spent the first ten years of his career trying to get out of sales. But then he realized what an important role he was playing for his organization on the front line as an ambassador for his brand. He has now developed a love for the craft of sales, and dedicates large portions of his life to training sales teams and solving sales challenges for all types of B2B businesses, from Fortune500 companies to start-ups on six continents.", "country": 141, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/df0919c6-6485-431c-b7b7-9cf2e0a30cf4-a05be814-2cd3-4e82-8e72-f328b200a169.png", "full_name": "Martin L.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1027167, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1027163, "description": "Sales strategy", "preview": false }, { "id": 1027164, "description": "Sales enablement", "preview": false }, { "id": 1027165, "description": "Sales incentives", "preview": false }, { "id": 1027166, "description": "Territory management", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 771391, "text": "

Which of the following should you bear in mind while doing this?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7369852, "text": "

You are based in the UK.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369853, "text": "

Your company has 320 employees.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369854, "text": "

Last year’s revenue was £500,000.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369855, "text": "

The company is called SAFE.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369856, "text": "

The conversion rate of similar solutions your company offers.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369857, "text": "

Your existing client base demographics.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1027167, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 771391, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 771398, "text": "

You’re working as a sales development representative at a consulting company. To build brand awareness, you use an automation tool to send cold emails to prospects. However, the open rate of these emails is 12%, much lower than the industry average of 21%.


Which action should you take to improve this?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7369858, "text": "

Review your email follow-up process.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369859, "text": "

Review the opening line of the body of the email template.

", "score": 2, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369860, "text": "

Review the subject line of the email template.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369861, "text": "

Review the signature on the email template.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1027167, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 2, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.002", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 771398, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 771399, "text": "

You’ve recently been appointed as the sales manager for Prospect.io. You’re responsible for managing a team of highly competent sales development representatives (SDRs) who set up meetings with prospects for your company’s account executives. Recently, the number of meetings booked has dropped.

 

Which actions should you take to understand the issue?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-response", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7369862, "text": "

Calculate the average deal size.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369863, "text": "

Calculate the cancellation rate.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369864, "text": "

Review the number of calls made.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369865, "text": "

Confirm the number of deals won.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7369866, "text": "

Examine the time to close deals.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 1027167, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 3, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.003", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 771399, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 771400, "text": "

You are the sales manager at a solar power company experiencing rapid growth. You’ve decided to look at setting up operations across the country, so you are developing a territory management strategy.

 

True or false: You should consider developing a customer segment definition strategy.

", "intro_text": null, "type": "truefalse", "shuffle": false, "answers": [ { "id": 7369867, "text": "

True

You have been outsourced by a prestigious university and need to analyze the quality of a new online course. ​​To carry out the research, the program manager asks you to survey only students who received high grades in the class, which is a minority.

 

What recommendation should you make to the program manager?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 6032605, "text": "

The survey should be applied to the same number of students with low grades as those with high grades.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6032606, "text": "

The survey should be applied only to the students who received a low grade to determine if the problem is related to the course.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6032607, "text": "

The survey should be applied to the course coordinators since they have the most direct, in-depth experience with the course.

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 6032608, "text": "

The survey should be applied to all participating students, including feedback from the coordinators.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false } ], "skill_area": 772948, "status": "active", "state": "new", "order": 1, "has_changed": false, "has_versions": false, "duration": 0, "previous_version": null, "identifier": "Q00.001", "code_language": null, "initial_code": null, "correct_code": "not-applicable", "return_type": "str", "function_name": null, "code_params": [], "code_test_cases": [], "sql_return_type": "SELECT", "initial_sql": null, "sql_test_cases": [], "typing_test_type": null, "typing_test_config": null, "typing_test_mode": { "numbers": false, "punctuation": false, "funbox": "none", "sentences": false }, "long_answer_list": false, "max_items": 100, "min_items": 0, "scale": 5, "custom_question_id": 464370, "what_to_look_for_in_the_answer": "", "why_is_this_question_relevant": "", "title": "", "category": [], "language": "en", "default_language": "en", "resources": [], "boilerplates": [], "programming_solutions": [], "test_cases": [], "test_version_number": 1 }, { "id": 464373, "text": "

{ "id": 1012236, "name": "Marketing Analytics", "summary": "This Marketing Analytics test evaluates a candidate’s ability to review and improve your marketing performance in a data-driven way. { "id": 1371858, "name": "Zoho CRM", "summary": "This Zoho CRM test assesses a candidate's competency using Zoho CRM, enabling you to hire individuals who can leverage Zoho CRM to streamline sales processes, automate workflows, generate insights, and optimize marketing strategies.", "duration": 600.0, "estimated_duration": null, "type": [ { "id": 8, "name": "Software skills", "visible": true } ], "is_new": false, "content_type_name": "test_authoring.test", "default_language": "en", "description": "Hiring candidates proficient in Zoho CRM offers a direct path to optimizing sales processes, nurturing customer relationships, streamlining workflows, and harnessing actionable insights to drive growth. \n\nThis Zoho CRM test evaluates candidates' competencies in four critical skill areas: setup and configuration, sales and marketing management, process automation and workflows, and reporting and analytics. Within this assessment, candidates are tested on their proficiency in configuring Zoho CRM, managing sales and marketing operations, automating critical processes, and effectively utilizing the reporting and analytics tools.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify individuals, such as CRM administrators, sales managers, and marketing professionals, who can harness Zoho CRM to deliver tangible results. These experts proficiently translate their knowledge into operational efficiency, enhanced customer engagement, and data-driven decision-making. Candidates who excel in this assessment demonstrate their potential to enhance your business's sales and marketing strategies, ensuring a competitive edge in today's dynamic market.", "relevant": "Sales representatives, sales managers, marketing managers, customer relationship managers, CRM administrators, customer support representatives, CRM analysts, and any other role that requires proficiency in this software.", "job_roles": [ 6008, 3332, 2171, 3369, 2243, 2246, 2270, 6142, 6232, 6148, 2381, 6029, 4594, 3573, 2576, 3578, 2669, 2687, 6052, 6180, 3692, 3713, 5592, 6320, 2828, 4961, 3800, 3823, 2951, 3077, 5160, 5161, 5162, 3898, 5163, 5164, 5165, 3899, 5166, 5984 ], "owner": { "id": 719133, "biography": "With expertise in DevOps engineering and project management, Jude also boasts in-depth knowledge and experience using the Zoho Suite in its entirety. Jude possesses many years’ experience as a consultant and automation expert for Web3 companies, and also brings expertise in managing SharePoint servers, deploying automation solutions, and ensuring effective Linux system administration. Jude is always looking for new challenges and is passionate about keeping up with developments in technology.", "country": null, "image": "https://tgo-public-assets-production.s3.amazonaws.com/production/ae9af26d-7f79-4b34-9c2b-e6d7629f0414-197f0ca7-dd9a-4053-aa40-e48996709e2c.jpeg", "full_name": "Jude O.", "url": null }, "level": "intermediate", "language": "en", "covered_skills": [ { "id": 1419195, "description": "Preview questions", "preview": true }, { "id": 1419191, "description": "Setup and configuration", "preview": false }, { "id": 1419192, "description": "Sales and marketing", "preview": false }, { "id": 1419193, "description": "Process automation and workflows", "preview": false }, { "id": 1419194, "description": "Reporting and analytics", "preview": false } ], "preview_questions": [ { "id": 1210090, "text": "

As a Zoho CRM specialist, you have a complex sales team structure with multiple roles. You've been tasked with ensuring that sales representatives in the same role can view and edit one another's leads to foster collaboration. However, you want to limit access to leads owned by sales representatives in different roles.


What step should you take to achieve this?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 10096841, "text": "

Create a sharing rule for cross-role lead access.

Candidates will be evaluated on their ability to identify potential markets, engage with their community, and develop effective community plans. Additionally, candidates will be tested on their ability to communicate and moderate effectively, including managing customer feedback and conflicts. Candidates will also be evaluated on their ability to manage content, including creating, deploying, and reviewing content. Finally, candidates will be tested on their ability to analyze data and analytics, including measuring success and KPIs, and analyzing trends in the community.\n\nThis screening test will help you identify social media community management professionals who have the necessary skills and experience to excel in your organization. What action should you take?

", "intro_text": null, "type": "multiple-choice", "shuffle": true, "answers": [ { "id": 7985738, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7985739, "text": "

", "score": 0, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7985740, "text": "

Answer all inquiries personally and provide relevant self-serve links in your responses.

", "score": 5, "rich_text": false }, { "id": 7985741, "text": "
